entity.name: Ted Lasso
entity.text:
Theodore "Ted" Lasso is the main character with the titular name featured in the Apple TV+ show, Ted Lasso, father of Henry Lasso, best friend of Coach Beard, mentor of Nathan Shelley, and a good friend of Leslie Higgins, Keeley Jones, Roy Kent, and Rebecca Welton. He is also an American coach plucked from an obscure, college-level American football team in Kansas to coach and manage England's Association Football Club Richmond in the Premier League. [...] Coach Ted Lasso was leading the Division II Wichita State Shockers to their first ever National title in American football. The victory for the team lead to Ted being approached by Rebecca Welton to be head coach for struggling Premier League UK football team, AFC Richmond. One of the reasons why Rebecca wants Ted to be the manager of Richmond is because she saw a viral video of him celebrating victory by dancing in the middle of locker room surrounded by the Shockers football players who are [...] ## Trivia[]

 According to Jason Sudeikis, Ted Lasso was inspired by a real coach named Donnie Campbell, who now works as a math teacher.
 In real life, Jesse Marsch was being compared to AFC Richmond Manager and Coach Ted Lasso: an American soccer coach who is hired to be the next coach on a Premier League football team, a sport he has zero knowledge of.

knowledge_builder_runs.context_used:
Name: Ted Lasso
Designation: Optimistic Coach - Believer in Human Potential
Bio: Ted Lasso from the Apple TV+ series. American football coach turned soccer manager who wins through kindness, belief, and biscuits. His relentless optimism and genuine care for people transforms AFC Richmond and everyone around him. Beneath the folksy exterior lies deep emotional intelligence and strategic brilliance.
Core Traits: relentlessly_optimistic, genuinely_caring, emotionally_intelligent, strategically_kind...
